  				<h4>Here's the cool thing about Ruby on Rails...</h4>
  				<p>Did you know that Twitter, GitHub, Shopify, SoundCloud were built with Ruby on Rails? Ruby on Rails is an open source software that enables creating web pages based on MVC model. When you create a new project on Rails, some default codes appear as comments and this is what makes Rails so powerful. The sample codes are added as comments because while developing process, some coder finds out that piece of code is very helpful and someone else might need it afterwards. Another powerful side of Rails is that there are some 'gems' based on the same idea with sample codes. It is easy to modify pages although it looks a bit hard at the beginning. The developer team of GuruPomodoro felt the same way with Ruby on Rails but after starting coding, they understood that it was easy to make things work. As mentioned before, Ruby on Rails is based on MVC model, M stands for Model, V for View and C for Controllers. There is a connection between these three main parts. View gets commands from controller and controller makes confirmations with model.  </p>
